claim.claim-text:
1. A process for manufacturing a connecting rod, comprising: 
placing a heated preform suitable for being formed into the connecting rod into a closed forge die; 
forging the preform in a first forging operation while the preform is at a forging temperature to form an as-forged connecting rod having vertical flash extending therefrom; 
placing the as-forged connecting rod in a second forge die while the as-forged connecting rod is at a temperature substantially equal to the forging temperature; 
forging the vertical flash in a second forging operation; 
removing the as-forged connecting rod from the second forge die; and 
machining the as-forged connecting rod to predetermined dimensions.
